                                <a name="tags"></a>

                <div class="news-list" id="news-content">
                    
                    <article class="news-item " id="article-240089">
    <div class="news-item-promo">
        <figure class="news-item-thumb">
            <a class="news-item-thumb-link" rel="bookmark" href="/news/youtube-seemingly-intentionally-crippled-and-slow-on-firefox-while-google-chrome-works-fine/">
                <img src="https://cdn.neowin.com/news/images/uploaded/2023/03/1677675425_youtube-frown_medium.jpg" alt="A YouTube frown on a dark background" width="360" height="203" />

                                                    
            </a>
        </figure>
        <header class="news-item-header">
            <h3 class="news-item-title">
                <a rel="bookmark" href="/news/youtube-seemingly-intentionally-crippled-and-slow-on-firefox-while-google-chrome-works-fine/">YouTube seemingly intentionally crippled and slow on Firefox while Google Chrome works fine</a>
            </h3>
            <p class="news-item-meta">
                <span class="author vcard">
                                        <a class="fn profile-link" rel="author" href="/profile/649440-sayan-sen/">Sayan Sen</a>
                                        &middot;
                </span>
                <time class="date published" datetime="2023-11-20T17:46:01+00:00">2 minutes ago</time>                                <span class="comments">
                    <span>with</span> <a href="/news/youtube-seemingly-intentionally-crippled-and-slow-on-firefox-while-google-chrome-works-fine/#comments" class="comment-link " title="View 0 Comments">0 <span>comments</span></a>
                </span>
            </p>
        </header>
    </div>
    <div class="news-item-content">
        <p>If you happen to use Firefox and you recently noticed YouTube loading up slowly on it, chances are it&#039;s not your internet or your hardwareâ€” Firefox itself allegedly causing the issue.</p>
    </div>
        <p class="news-item-meta-mobile">
